Amazon CloudFront is AWS’s global Content Delivery Network (CDN) service. It securely delivers data, videos, applications, and APIs to users worldwide with low latency and high transfer speeds by caching content at AWS edge locations.

🌐 Key Features
Global Edge Network: Uses hundreds of edge locations worldwide to serve content closer to users.
Caching: Reduces load on origin servers (like S3, EC2, or on-premises).
Security Integration: Works with AWS WAF, Shield, and ACM for DDoS protection and HTTPS.
Dynamic & Static Content: Optimized for both static files (images, CSS, JS) and dynamic APIs.
Customizable Routing: Supports geo-restriction, signed URLs, and signed cookies.
Origin Flexibility: Can pull content from AWS services or external servers.

✅ Use Cases
Website Acceleration: Cache static assets (images, CSS, JS) for faster page loads.
Video Streaming: Deliver live or on-demand video globally.
API Distribution: Securely deliver APIs with low latency.
E-commerce: Handle global traffic spikes during sales events.
Security: Protect applications with WAF + Shield integration.

